{
  "texts": [
    "On the other hand, there were some students who initially began to engage more thoughtfully with AI in the first session but reverted to seeking direct answers in the second and third sessions.",
    "This reversion could reflect a preference for efficiency and straightforward solutions, possibly driven by the demands of the task or time constraints, which is also discussed in previous research on learner behavior in digital environments (Beaudoin, 2002; Ellis & Bliuc, 2016).",
    "It might also suggest that while the training and guidance provided an initial boost in effective AI usage, its impact may have diminished over time, or that some students found it easier to return to a more passive role in their interactions with AI.",
    "The significant impact of previous programming knowledge on students' AI interaction profiles in the initial activity session emphasizes the role of foundational understanding in shaping how students engage with AI tools.",
    "The findings of the current study have demonstrated that students with higher previous programming knowledge were more likely to adopt the AI-Assisted Code Refiner profile compared to the AI-Reliant Code Generator profile."
  ]
}